Re. “Rob’s hockey legacy gets ’big honour’ at Fan Fest,” Aug. 22

I would like to ask Sebastian, the friend who wishes to be called Bob and who defends Mayor Rob Ford for stealing a donor puck and turning it slowly by the stands “to show his how his city got down to eye level” — are you aware that you are completely deluded if you think we too are nutritionally deficient and cannot see? Do you know that your ignorance has nothing to do with brain size — you know enough about that from your city’s mayor — and that Hubert Reeves said, “It is because we see with a signal coming from a small part of the retina called the fovea centralis, almost without colour or shade variation or information of slight differences in brightness, that our visual images resemble the impressions we get from staring at a postage stamp.”

S. Mary Diefenbaker, Toronto
